colName: # Number and proportion (among all responses) of high and low TP chunk

meaning: Number of high TP chunks. High TP chunks are defined as two-syllabic chunk from a word
label: Number of High-TP chunks

label: Proportion of High-TP chunks among productions

label: Number of Low-TP chunks

label: Number of Low-TP chunks among productions

colName: # Average forward TPs and difference from expected TP

meaning: Average (across recalled items) of average forward TPs among transitions in a given item.
label: Forward TPs

meaning: Average (across recalled items) of the difference between the average ACTUAL forward TPs among transitions in a given item and the EXPECTED forward TP in that item, based on the items first element. See calculate.expected.tps.for.chunks for the calculations
label: Actual vs. expected forward TPs

meaning: Average (across recalled items) of average backward TPs among transitions in a given item.
label: Backward TPs
